The paper deals with self-healing in reconfigurable networks, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and networked systems (cs.NI). The algorithm proposed in the paper is fully distributed, which further supports the classification under cs.DC. The paper also discusses the expansion and spectral properties of the network, which are topics related to theoretical computer science (cs.THE) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes a distributed data structure with low latency and bandwidth requirements, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.SI).
